 class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yurpean@nuclearspace>Yurpean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/19/03 1:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=794.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   iron ships, men of wood</span><hr size=1> It used to be the other way around! Unfortunately the welfare state changed all of that. Look at all those politicians and media people claiming the risks are too high to fly in space. They're GETTING PAID to say these things and their only function is to say them: everyone can say &quot;continu&quot; but you need real knowledge to make that happen. Should you not possess that knowledge and your aim is to influence things you should say &quot;No, wait a minute&quot;. <br>
These people are unnecessary government-sponsored ballast that should be dropped in the slums somewhere. As a result of their actions the ships turn into iron, becoming less able to take off, and the men turn into wooden doubters losing their will to make a difference.<br>
One good example of this was on Dutch television today of a truck driver who likened driving through a (relatively short) tunnel to &quot;venturing into the unknown&quot;, &quot;I don't know what to expect&quot; he exclaimed worrying about some very remote catastrophe. <br>
Wood is something you chop off a tree and use to make a big fire. Seems to be time for a really big fire <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 345<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/19/03 1:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=794.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: iron ships, men of wood</span><hr size=1> The media, while at times annoying, is vital to the spread of information.  Without the spread of free information, you get a dictatorship.<br>
<br>
And, at least in America, the media is not paid by the government.  Sorry!<br>
<br>
But I agree with your sentiment.  Society is no longer willing to take risks, and everything has to be 100% certain before we do something.  While risks should be mitigated beforehand if possible, we shouldn't balk at any risk!  We can't spend decades to develop a risk-free system, it just doesn't exist.<br>
<br>
So why not accept the risk and move on? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A> at: 2/19/03 2:00:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=x@nuclearspace>X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/19/03 7:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=794.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: iron ships, men of wood</span><hr size=1> I disagree.  Remember, most people living during the 1600's didn't and wouldn't make the trip to America.  Those few that did come would be considered today as cultists (Pilgrims, Quakers, etc), criminals (the colony of ex-cons from the debters' prison in Georgia and the criminal colony in Australia), and trailer trash (those who came to escape poverty).  It's only when the frontier was tamed did the majority of the immigrants come.  No, it takes the dredges of society of settle the new frontier while the normal people stay at home. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NS Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 941<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/19/03 9:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=794.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: iron ships, men of wood</span><hr size=1> The problem, like Yurpean was hinting at, is that the mainstream media isn't free enough.  This is one of the few things I agree with Noam Chomsky on.  Whether the mass media is government controlled, like in some countries, or corporate controlled, the news is always going to be biased in some fashion or another.  What I like about the internet and forums like this one is that its a more free form of info exchange.  I also agree with Yurpean and X that we're turning into a bunch of softies with no vision for opening frontiers anymore.  Humanity needs new frontiers to thrive or society just starts to stagnate and go down hill.  I believe we're already well into the latter process.     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/19/03 9:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=794.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: iron ships, men of wood</span><hr size=1> I kind of hinted at that second point.  But yes, media does have bias, but it is usually balanced by the audience, at least in a capitalist system where the media caters to its consumers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=794.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=794.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=794.topic&index=4><img 